node.title: Victoria has recorded 980 new local COVID-19 cases and seven deaths
node.alt: A male nurse gives a vaccine to a girl wearing a face mask.
node.description: There are now 15,433 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 554 people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 980\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and seven\u00a0deaths, as Australia's Therapeutic Goods Administration (TGA)\u00a0provisionally approves\u00a0the Pfizer vaccine for children aged between five and 11 years of age.", "There are now 15,433\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 554\u00a0people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.\u00a0", "There are 299\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 40\u00a0are in intensive care and 16\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "Victoria's\u00a0Health Department said a further 43\u00a0people were in intensive care but their COVID-19 infections were no longer considered active.", "The new cases were detected from 65,449\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 2,625\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, and more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "Victoria has now fully vaccinated around 91\u00a0per cent of its population aged 12 years or older.", "More to come.", "", "
Heavily mutated Omicron variant puts scientist on alert
"]
